WEBVTT

00:07.417 --> 00:08.625
Thank you, New York.

00:08.708 --> 00:10.875
-[indistinct cheering]
-It's humbling to be sitting here,

00:10.958 --> 00:13.500
speaking to you as Mayor this evening.

00:13.583 --> 00:16.542
-[Vanessa] I need a favor.
-You want me to kill someone?

00:16.625 --> 00:17.667
[Vanessa] Foggy Nelson.

00:18.458 --> 00:20.000
[gun cocks]

00:20.083 --> 00:21.208
Looking for--

00:21.292 --> 00:22.333
[gasps] Foggy!

00:22.417 --> 00:25.625
[Matt] I went to Rikers.
Ben Poindexter wanted to meet me.

00:25.708 --> 00:26.708
[groans]

00:26.792 --> 00:29.042
[Heather] What were
you thinking, Matt? Him?

00:29.667 --> 00:30.958
[Matt] Yeah.

00:31.042 --> 00:34.083
[Heather] You know what? I don't care.
It's fine. It's none of my business.

00:34.667 --> 00:37.500
-[gun fires]
-[people screaming]

00:41.042 --> 00:42.125
Karen?

00:43.417 --> 00:46.917
Matt, you have been checking out on me,

00:47.000 --> 00:50.542
disappearing physically and emotionally.

00:50.625 --> 00:52.708
[Matt] Back at his place,
I heard your heartbeats.

00:52.792 --> 00:54.625
[Karen] You hear mine when I saw you?

00:54.708 --> 00:56.375
Adrenaline, I'm sure.

00:56.458 --> 00:57.958
[Karen] Foggy believed in you.

00:58.042 --> 01:01.000
Whatever's behind the mask,
behind your eyes,

01:01.083 --> 01:03.958
he knew all of it, he knew you. I do, too.

01:04.042 --> 01:05.250
[Matt] I'm glad you're back.

01:05.333 --> 01:06.333
[kisses]

01:06.417 --> 01:07.750
Cherry is your hatchet man?

01:07.833 --> 01:09.708
-[Matt] He's my investigator.
-Morning, Officer.

01:09.792 --> 01:12.542
I sit atop a pyramid of over 500 ADAs.

01:12.625 --> 01:15.042
You're not gonna be able to
stumble into traffic court

01:15.125 --> 01:16.375
without one up your ass.

01:16.458 --> 01:18.625
BB. Is that short for something?

01:18.708 --> 01:19.917
I was named for my uncle.

01:20.000 --> 01:21.167
Ben Urich.

01:21.250 --> 01:23.792
[Chief Gallo] Do you know that Wilson Fisk

01:23.875 --> 01:26.375
was the main suspect
in your uncle's murder?

01:26.458 --> 01:28.875
[BB] Why do you think I'm here?

01:29.458 --> 01:31.583
Not everything I write is under my name.

01:31.667 --> 01:34.250
So if you ever want to
put anything real out there,

01:34.333 --> 01:36.000
there's an email on this card.

01:37.000 --> 01:40.958
[Buck] Dr. Glenn, allow me to introduce
Mayor and Mrs. Fisk.

01:41.042 --> 01:42.333
I would like for you to be

01:42.417 --> 01:45.167
my administration's
Commissioner of Mental Health.

01:45.250 --> 01:46.875
[grunting, groaning]

01:48.292 --> 01:49.500
[Heather] It would be my honor.

01:49.583 --> 01:52.083
You are aware of
the rumors that surround you?

01:52.167 --> 01:54.208
Shall I call you Swordsman?

01:54.292 --> 01:55.292
Is that a threat?

01:55.375 --> 01:57.792
[Fisk] Of course not.
It's merely a warning.

01:57.875 --> 01:59.792
[grunting in pain]

02:00.458 --> 02:01.875
[Fisk] This city is in a crisis.

02:01.958 --> 02:06.250
Consider yourself founding members
of my Anti-Vigilante Task Force.

02:06.333 --> 02:07.542
[grunting]

02:07.625 --> 02:10.958
There will be no body cams,
no due process, no warrants!

02:11.042 --> 02:15.708
And in the immediate future,
curfew is at 8:00 p.m.

02:15.792 --> 02:18.000
New York City is under martial law.

02:18.083 --> 02:19.917
I'm gonna take this city back, Karen.

02:21.625 --> 02:22.833
[Karen] Where do we start?

02:30.333 --> 02:32.583
[indistinct chatter, laughter]

02:33.708 --> 02:35.958
[BB] So, did Mayor Fisk fix it?

02:36.042 --> 02:37.042
Yeah.

02:38.083 --> 02:41.083
You know, I read the papers,
see the numbers that, like,

02:41.167 --> 02:43.917
violent crime is down, way down.
Property crime, too.

02:44.000 --> 02:46.333
But screw the papers.

02:46.417 --> 02:49.750
You can feel it.
New York is back and better than ever.

02:54.875 --> 02:58.292
[waves crashing]

03:01.250 --> 03:04.917
[ship horn blaring]

03:32.958 --> 03:35.792
[breathing heavily]

03:36.833 --> 03:39.958
[indistinct, overlapping voices]

03:45.917 --> 03:47.583
[metallic thump]

03:53.250 --> 03:54.500
[gasps, grunts]

04:09.583 --> 04:11.583
[both grunting]

04:12.917 --> 04:15.333
[rattling]

04:28.833 --> 04:30.417
[grunts, groans]

04:37.417 --> 04:39.417
[guard 1 speaks Cypriot Greek]

04:39.500 --> 04:41.375
[guard 2 in English] Go, go, go, go, go.

04:44.125 --> 04:46.542
[Daredevil yelling]

04:48.042 --> 04:49.042
[guard 3] Find him!

04:51.125 --> 04:54.125
[all grunting]

05:14.708 --> 05:16.583
[monitor beeping]

05:21.833 --> 05:22.875
[Achilleo exhales heavily]

05:22.958 --> 05:25.208
[machinery whirring]

05:25.292 --> 05:27.292
[engine powering down]

05:39.000 --> 05:40.833
[breathing heavily]

05:42.417 --> 05:43.875
[beeping]

05:44.667 --> 05:47.750
[alarms blaring]

05:56.583 --> 05:57.958
[grunting]

06:08.292 --> 06:10.667
[breathing heavily]

06:16.792 --> 06:18.500
[Achilleo] They're going to come for us.

06:37.125 --> 06:38.417
[alarm rings]

06:38.500 --> 06:40.333
[alarm blaring]

06:43.583 --> 06:45.500
[breathing heavily]

06:54.833 --> 06:57.458
[breathing steadily]

06:57.542 --> 07:00.500
[overlapping sounds]

07:00.583 --> 07:02.583
[watch ticking]

07:11.375 --> 07:13.917
[breathing heavily]

07:19.917 --> 07:21.542
[grunting]

07:26.500 --> 07:27.708
[yells]

07:45.458 --> 07:47.542
[panting heavily]

08:12.542 --> 08:14.542
[♪ theme music playing]

09:54.333 --> 09:56.833
[police siren wailing in distance]

09:57.833 --> 09:59.667
[glass crunching]

10:03.792 --> 10:07.667
[soft grunting]

10:07.750 --> 10:10.375
[woman's breaths echoing]

10:11.542 --> 10:13.583
[soft grunting continues]

10:22.833 --> 10:25.333
[woman breathing heavily]

10:31.083 --> 10:33.167
[Karen] Northern Star
is all over the news.

10:33.250 --> 10:35.000
You definitely sent Fisk a message.

10:35.083 --> 10:36.792
Your source was right. This is big.

10:37.417 --> 10:38.750
It's a crack in Fisk's armor.

10:38.833 --> 10:41.833
The boat was full of weapons.
Rocket launchers, assault rifles.

10:41.917 --> 10:44.333
-Military grade. European, I think.
-Holy shit.

10:44.417 --> 10:46.250
He's using the Freeport to smuggle arms.

10:47.333 --> 10:49.667
-I think we hit him hard.
-Good.

10:50.792 --> 10:52.167
Fisk's gonna lose his mind.

10:52.792 --> 10:54.708
Yeah, I just can't help but wonder
what is,

10:54.792 --> 10:57.375
who is all that firepower for?

10:57.458 --> 10:59.375
You know who could find out.

11:00.042 --> 11:01.542
Yeah, yeah, give her a call.

11:04.125 --> 11:07.000
We get the message out there
that the mayor is running guns.

11:07.083 --> 11:10.250
The weapons, all of it, still on board,
just outside the port.

11:10.333 --> 11:11.333
So, what's next?

11:12.542 --> 11:13.542
Proving it.

11:13.625 --> 11:16.333
Okay, well,
I'm pretty sure I could help with that.

11:16.417 --> 11:17.417
Oh, yeah?

11:18.292 --> 11:19.958
I'm kinda counting on it, Miss Page.

11:26.625 --> 11:28.708
I need to call in a favor
with Metro General?

11:28.792 --> 11:29.833
No.

11:29.917 --> 11:31.042
Stitches?

11:31.667 --> 11:32.667
No.

11:33.292 --> 11:35.292
Then I guess
tonight was a pretty good night.

11:37.875 --> 11:38.958
It could get better.

11:39.042 --> 11:40.208
[Karen giggles]

11:56.042 --> 11:59.583
Harbor Control confirms that the wreck
is blocking the entrance to the port.

11:59.667 --> 12:02.208
Nothing is landing
until the Northern Star is cleared.

12:04.917 --> 12:07.333
Perishables are being diverted
to New Jersey.

12:37.750 --> 12:39.542
This is a terrorist attack.

12:41.542 --> 12:45.708
Orchestrated and executed
by the vigilante of Hell's Kitchen.

12:48.625 --> 12:51.542
Uh, yeah,
I think I can get that out there.

12:51.625 --> 12:55.083
Powell, I want you to organize
the salvage operation.

12:55.167 --> 12:58.292
Copy that.
I'll have a crew for you by morning.

12:58.375 --> 13:01.292
The hunt for Daredevil and Karen Page,
intensify it.

13:01.375 --> 13:02.417
Yes, sir.

13:02.500 --> 13:03.500
[Fisk] Buck...

13:05.750 --> 13:08.708
Who knew what was in that ship
besides you and I?

13:08.792 --> 13:10.958
Only the captain and the first mate, sir.

13:13.083 --> 13:14.083
Find them.

13:22.833 --> 13:24.500
[tapping on glass]

13:30.167 --> 13:32.333
[cell phone vibrating]

13:32.417 --> 13:34.417
[man gulps, exhales]

13:37.083 --> 13:38.417
[exhales] Yeah, it's me.

13:39.125 --> 13:40.750
Yeah, I'm watching.

13:42.542 --> 13:47.625
Yeah, I would say
"clusterfuck" is a pretty apt description.

13:49.958 --> 13:52.333
No, no, it's fine.
I'll go up there myself.

13:54.792 --> 13:56.042
I need the miles.

13:59.125 --> 14:00.417
[cell phone beeps]

14:10.250 --> 14:11.792
[BB] So, what do you think?

14:11.875 --> 14:15.083
-Mayor Fisk is gonna clean that up.
-I worry about the pollution.

14:15.167 --> 14:17.958
Babe, this is the East River, okay?
It's nasty.

14:18.042 --> 14:20.875
There's diapers floating there.
The masked bastards worry me.

14:20.958 --> 14:24.542
I don't care what he needs to do.
Lockdowns, task force,

14:24.625 --> 14:26.083
throw the book at 'em, whatever.

14:26.167 --> 14:28.792
If these animals
can do something like that...

14:28.875 --> 14:30.208
[scoffs] ...what's next?

14:31.708 --> 14:33.583
[Karen] Fisk is losing his mind.

14:33.667 --> 14:36.500
It'll probably take me a bit longer
to meet up with my sources.

14:36.583 --> 14:38.875
Let's make it four o'clock?

14:39.542 --> 14:42.375
If you're not back by 5:00,
I'll meet you at the fallback spot.

14:42.458 --> 14:43.750
[Karen sighs]

14:43.833 --> 14:45.250
You okay?

14:45.333 --> 14:47.333
I mean, just fucking every time, Matt.

14:48.458 --> 14:50.750
No matter how we come at him,
no matter what we do,

14:50.833 --> 14:52.375
-Fisk just gets back up.
-[chuckles]

14:52.458 --> 14:53.917
Even worse than before.

14:54.000 --> 14:56.000
Yeah, that's why
we have to keep trying, huh?

14:56.625 --> 14:57.667
Yeah.

14:58.458 --> 15:00.375
We expose that he's running guns,

15:00.458 --> 15:03.250
he's using the Freeport
to line his and his cronies' pockets.

15:04.417 --> 15:07.250
Show the city,
show Albany who he is and...

15:08.208 --> 15:09.625
he will be held accountable.

15:15.083 --> 15:16.417
I have to believe that, Kare.

15:20.875 --> 15:22.708
[cell phone vibrating]

15:25.333 --> 15:27.542
-[cell phone beeping]
-Jess just pulled the ship's manifest.

15:28.500 --> 15:30.458
Well, she get who he's smuggling guns for?

15:30.542 --> 15:32.500
Uh... No,

15:32.583 --> 15:35.458
but for now we have the captain
and the first mate.

15:36.375 --> 15:40.083
Both Cypriot nationals
and both have family in Astoria.

15:40.958 --> 15:41.958
I'll check it out.

15:42.042 --> 15:43.167
-Okay.
-Hey, be careful.

15:49.542 --> 15:50.583
[door creaks]

15:52.167 --> 15:54.708
[Fisk breathing heavily]

15:59.708 --> 16:00.708
[Sheila] They're here, sir.

16:03.458 --> 16:05.250
It's good to see you again, Mr. Gomez.

16:06.375 --> 16:09.917
You haven't met the Attorney General yet,
have you, Mayor Fisk?

16:10.000 --> 16:11.375
No, I have not.

16:11.458 --> 16:13.792
Certainly not for the lack of trying,
I might add.

16:13.875 --> 16:16.250
I have my hands full here in New York.

16:16.333 --> 16:20.250
Which is why we are here, actually.

16:20.333 --> 16:22.833
[AG Steverud] You've given yourself
extraordinary emergency powers.

16:22.917 --> 16:26.583
Your Safer Streets initiative
equates vigilantes with terrorists?

16:26.667 --> 16:29.292
[Gomez] Imposing mandatory life sentences

16:29.375 --> 16:32.417
on anyone convicted of
extra-judicial actions.

16:32.500 --> 16:34.042
Your point being?

16:34.125 --> 16:36.458
My point is that
these are provocative moves, Mr. Mayor.

16:36.542 --> 16:38.667
Moves that weren't discussed
with the Governor,

16:38.750 --> 16:40.375
weren't discussed with myself.

16:40.458 --> 16:43.750
Yeah, and now you got a ship
capsized in the East River.

16:46.750 --> 16:49.167
Please tell the Governor that the culprit

16:49.250 --> 16:52.875
will be brought to justice
loudly, visibly.

16:53.667 --> 16:56.375
I vowed to clean up the streets
and I've done that.

16:56.458 --> 16:58.750
[AG Steverud] Listen, Wilson,
all I'm trying to say is that

16:58.833 --> 17:01.375
there will be a lot of scrutiny
with the Vigilante Trials.

17:01.458 --> 17:03.250
My office needs to be involved.

17:03.333 --> 17:06.125
I know you're not gonna like it,
but that means oversight.

17:06.208 --> 17:08.333
-[door opens]
-Uh, okay. Hi. Sorry I'm late.

17:08.417 --> 17:10.542
Do you know they have a Gyro King
in Manhattan?

17:10.625 --> 17:13.292
The line around the cart was, like,
it was insane,

17:13.375 --> 17:15.667
but look at this thing.
It's a pound of food.

17:15.750 --> 17:17.542
-[Sheila] Excuse me.
-Yes?

17:17.625 --> 17:20.292
Uh, I don't know why security let you in,

17:20.375 --> 17:22.542
or if you're even supposed to be here.

17:25.917 --> 17:28.167
I am definitely supposed to
be here, Sheila.

17:33.333 --> 17:35.000
And Mr...

17:35.083 --> 17:37.292
Charles. Mr. Charles.

17:37.958 --> 17:41.250
Um... Well, where are you from?

17:42.500 --> 17:43.917
Um...

17:44.000 --> 17:45.625
So good. Langley.

17:48.583 --> 17:51.875
I don't what you or the agency
thinks that you're doing here, but--

17:51.958 --> 17:55.000
Well, I don't know
what a Lieutenant Governor actually is,

17:55.083 --> 17:57.458
so I guess we're even, aren't we, Juan?

17:57.542 --> 17:59.250
[soft laughter]

17:59.333 --> 18:01.000
[AG Steverud] Well, whoever you are...

18:01.083 --> 18:03.917
-we will not be intimidated.
-[cell phone vibrating]

18:04.000 --> 18:06.792
You're definitely gonna wanna
answer that phone call.

18:10.292 --> 18:12.250
-[cell phone beeps]
-Steverud.

18:15.667 --> 18:16.708
Oh?

18:18.875 --> 18:20.125
Yeah, I totally understand.

18:21.667 --> 18:22.792
Yes, Miss de Fontaine.

18:26.958 --> 18:28.000
[exhales softly]

18:29.000 --> 18:32.708
As I was saying, Mr. Fisk,
my office will totally support you

18:32.792 --> 18:39.375
and your policies regarding vigilantism,
Safer Streets, hell, all of it.

18:41.208 --> 18:42.208
[Fisk] Oversight?

18:42.875 --> 18:44.083
[AG Steverud] Won't be a problem.

18:47.208 --> 18:49.208
I appreciate that very much.

18:50.875 --> 18:52.833
[ship horn blares in distance]

18:54.750 --> 18:56.375
[seagulls squawking]

19:26.542 --> 19:29.458
[Jack] Your mayor has
an interesting take on jurisprudence.

19:30.250 --> 19:33.792
I ask for a lawyer
and I get a psychiatrist.

19:34.583 --> 19:35.833
[Heather chuckles softly]

19:36.458 --> 19:40.083
This evaluation is for your legal team
at Murdock and McDuffie...

19:40.958 --> 19:42.500
as well as the District Attorney.

19:43.292 --> 19:44.958
I'm just an impartial observer here.

19:45.042 --> 19:48.458
Oh, please, Dr. Glenn. Impartial?

19:48.542 --> 19:49.625
That's cheeky.

19:51.250 --> 19:52.833
And where exactly is...

19:55.042 --> 19:56.042
"here"?

19:57.167 --> 20:01.458
Well, in the case of
adults dressing up in costume

20:01.542 --> 20:03.625
and fighting with the police,

20:03.708 --> 20:06.000
it seems a psychological evaluation
is in order.

20:06.083 --> 20:09.958
An absurd accusation
which I categorically deny.

20:10.917 --> 20:12.375
[sniffles softly]

20:14.208 --> 20:15.667
Mr. Duquesne, are you saying

20:15.750 --> 20:18.417
that you're not the vigilante
known as The Swordsman?

20:18.917 --> 20:20.167
I'm saying

20:20.250 --> 20:23.542
District Attorney Hochberg
will have to prove that in court.

20:28.917 --> 20:31.292
[Heather] I'm gonna ask you
some true or false questions.

20:31.375 --> 20:34.917
There's no wrong answer.
Please answer truthfully.

20:35.000 --> 20:36.083
True or false?

20:36.167 --> 20:38.292
"I like mechanics magazines."

20:38.375 --> 20:40.250
This is a waste of both our time.

20:41.208 --> 20:45.500
If a psychological evaluation is needed,
I prefer it be done by a professional

20:45.583 --> 20:49.042
agreed upon by both the prosecution
and the defense.

20:49.667 --> 20:51.875
I know the law, Dr. Glenn.

21:06.292 --> 21:07.333
Do you?

21:09.083 --> 21:12.083
Then you know you're being held here
under the Safer Streets Act.

21:12.875 --> 21:14.750
You're not at Rikers.

21:14.833 --> 21:17.125
The NYPD has no jurisdiction
over this place,

21:17.208 --> 21:19.417
or any knowledge of your whereabouts.

21:20.083 --> 21:22.708
Those two men outside
can do whatever they please to you,

21:22.792 --> 21:23.875
should I ask them to.

21:24.458 --> 21:26.250
And your trial,

21:26.333 --> 21:29.250
the only thing that might ever enable you
to see the light of day

21:29.333 --> 21:30.458
can be postponed...

21:31.583 --> 21:32.750
until you heal.

21:33.500 --> 21:35.125
Or canceled if you don't.

21:37.083 --> 21:38.458
True or false?

21:38.542 --> 21:40.250
"I like mechanics magazines."

21:40.333 --> 21:41.667
[Jack sighs]

21:45.958 --> 21:47.125
False.

21:49.958 --> 21:52.583
If you're calling about a relative
detained by Task Force,

21:52.667 --> 21:54.292
I'll have to put you on hold.

21:54.375 --> 21:56.292
How long since
you've last heard from them?

21:56.375 --> 21:58.708
[continues indistinctly]

22:02.042 --> 22:03.958
I need you to look into those for me
if you can.

22:04.042 --> 22:05.208
[Cherry sighs]

22:05.958 --> 22:08.583
One investigator
can't be expected to handle--

22:08.667 --> 22:12.333
Fisk targets people who can't pay
and we can't afford another investigator.

22:12.417 --> 22:13.917
And you can't afford to pay me.

22:14.000 --> 22:15.083
I know.

22:16.583 --> 22:19.292
-This is real David and Goliath shit.
-I ain't got a sling.

22:19.375 --> 22:23.500
Look, half of these pickups
are Task Force pickups.

22:23.583 --> 22:25.750
These people
just tend to disappear, Kirsten.

22:26.958 --> 22:28.583
Then we need to find them.

22:29.708 --> 22:30.708
[Cherry sighs]

22:34.292 --> 22:35.292
Anything?

22:36.875 --> 22:38.833
Nah, no, nothing, nada.

22:43.208 --> 22:45.333
Matt's gonna be fine, okay?
He's gonna be fine.

22:46.208 --> 22:49.208
Oh... He's just...
He's just gonna be fine?

22:50.333 --> 22:52.167
My partner, my friend goes missing--

22:52.250 --> 22:53.667
Oh, shit.

22:53.750 --> 22:55.292
Hochberg.

22:55.375 --> 22:57.500
-Detective Cherry.
-[Cherry] I'm retired.

22:57.583 --> 22:59.917
I'll honor the badge
in whatever form it comes.

23:00.542 --> 23:02.583
Could I speak with
Miss McDuffie privately?

23:06.958 --> 23:07.958
[beeps]

23:08.708 --> 23:10.625
Yeah, I was just on my way out.

23:11.792 --> 23:13.000
You good?

23:13.083 --> 23:15.042
Yeah. Never better.

23:17.542 --> 23:20.500
-Not exactly a white-shoe firm these days.
-[chuckles]

23:20.583 --> 23:24.042
More of a, I don't know, legal aid hostel.

23:24.125 --> 23:26.583
Yeah. Yeah.

23:27.875 --> 23:30.667
At least I get to keep my soul
at the end of the day.

23:30.750 --> 23:33.375
Kirsten, we both know
I don't need to be here.

23:33.458 --> 23:34.958
I came because I respect you.

23:35.625 --> 23:38.042
You were one of my best,
and I want to save you

23:38.125 --> 23:41.083
from an avalanche
of career-ending embarrassment.

23:42.625 --> 23:43.625
Plead out.

23:44.333 --> 23:46.958
Avoid the humiliation
of losing the Duquesne case.

23:48.167 --> 23:49.167
Oh, Ben.

23:50.333 --> 23:53.417
I have four brothers.
I don't get embarrassed.

23:54.125 --> 23:55.167
But thank you.

23:55.250 --> 23:58.042
Thank you very much for,
you know, caring about my career.

23:59.792 --> 24:02.625
My defenses are rock solid
and I have the evidence to prove it.

24:02.708 --> 24:06.583
Oh. You... You think the evidence matters?

24:08.917 --> 24:09.917
Wow.

24:11.083 --> 24:12.583
What happened to you?

24:15.500 --> 24:16.667
I read the tea leaves.

24:18.667 --> 24:20.750
Kirsten, come back to the DA's Office.

24:21.667 --> 24:24.375
I'll match whatever lie
you tell me you're making here.

24:26.667 --> 24:29.458
Well, you know,
it's a very generous offer,

24:29.542 --> 24:31.708
and I must respectfully say...

24:32.625 --> 24:33.667
fuck you!

24:35.667 --> 24:37.667
Well, that's disappointing, Kirsten.

24:37.750 --> 24:39.208
And I really prefer...

24:40.333 --> 24:41.375
Counselor McDuffie.

24:41.458 --> 24:44.375
I'll see you in court, Counselor McDuffie.

24:45.292 --> 24:46.792
[Kirsten] Sure as shit you will.

24:49.292 --> 24:50.375
[sniffles softly]

24:54.583 --> 24:56.917
[Cherry] I'm surprised to see you out here
so publicly.

24:57.000 --> 24:59.417
[Matt] Yeah, it's important.
The ship, the Northern Star.

24:59.958 --> 25:01.458
Yeah, I had a feeling you're behind this.

25:01.542 --> 25:04.042
It's loaded with military weapons.
Heavy-duty ordnance.

25:05.125 --> 25:08.333
-[sighs] Christ. Who is he in bed with?
-I'm working on that.

25:08.417 --> 25:11.333
He's obviously making money
for more than just his rich friends.

25:11.417 --> 25:13.542
This is our best chance to expose him.

25:13.625 --> 25:16.667
Fisk will move the weapons
before we can link him to the ship.

25:16.750 --> 25:18.542
You sank his ship for Christ's sake.

25:18.625 --> 25:20.333
I mean, here's a guy that would kill

25:20.417 --> 25:22.583
if someone's rude to his wife, and this...

25:22.667 --> 25:24.833
Fisk will destroy the whole city.

25:25.625 --> 25:26.917
You know I'm retired, right?

25:29.458 --> 25:31.292
Men died on that boat, Cherry.

25:32.125 --> 25:34.917
You and Kirsten are getting pretty good
at laying the guilt, you know that?

25:35.000 --> 25:38.292
[chuckles] It's 'cause it works.
How is she?

25:39.292 --> 25:42.708
[sighs] She's worried about you.
Would it kill you to reach out to her?

25:42.792 --> 25:43.917
I can't put her at risk.

25:44.792 --> 25:46.417
-And me?
-You're old.

25:47.250 --> 25:48.958
-Fuck you!
-Hey...

25:50.000 --> 25:52.125
I've been a target
since that night at Josie's.

25:52.750 --> 25:55.292
You know who I am
and you've never let me down.

25:55.375 --> 25:56.625
That's why I come to you.

25:56.708 --> 25:58.708
That's why I'm gonna keep coming to you.

25:58.792 --> 26:00.625
All right, all right, all right, so...

26:01.458 --> 26:03.292
Northern Star, what do you need from me?

26:03.375 --> 26:05.958
Captain and the First Mate
flooded the boat and took off.

26:06.042 --> 26:07.958
They're co-conspirators
in the gun-running.

26:08.042 --> 26:10.500
Achilleo Kyriaco and Christofi Savva.

26:12.292 --> 26:13.958
You need me to spell those names?

26:14.625 --> 26:16.542
Yeah, I need you to spell those names.

26:19.250 --> 26:20.750
[alarm blaring]

26:23.333 --> 26:25.542
[agent 1] Let's get them. Let's go.

26:26.083 --> 26:27.083
[agent 2] Go.

26:27.167 --> 26:28.708
[agent 3] Move away from the fucking door.

26:28.792 --> 26:30.083
What are you looking at? Move away.

26:30.167 --> 26:31.167
Go, go!

26:33.500 --> 26:35.292
-Move, move.
-[agent 4] Clear the fuck out.

26:36.417 --> 26:38.500
-Let's go!
-[people chattering]

26:45.792 --> 26:47.792
I'm looking for either of these two men.

26:48.958 --> 26:50.833
This is supposed to be one of their spots.

26:50.917 --> 26:53.333
I'm sorry. My English...

26:53.417 --> 26:55.667
Don't fucking do that. Yes or no?

27:01.000 --> 27:02.000
Right.

27:03.625 --> 27:05.000
-[grunts]
-[Ariana groans]

27:05.083 --> 27:06.333
There, there, there.

27:08.500 --> 27:09.583
[grunting]

27:14.000 --> 27:16.708
[gasps, panting]

27:23.042 --> 27:24.292
[gasps, grunts]

27:28.250 --> 27:29.292
[grunts]

27:29.375 --> 27:31.708
-[indistinct radio chatter]
-[Powell exhales heavily]

27:34.167 --> 27:35.250
[spits]

27:37.083 --> 27:39.333
New York is back and better than ever.

27:39.417 --> 27:41.583
-[chuckles]
-[♪ upbeat music playing]

27:41.667 --> 27:42.750
[cameraman] Oh, shit.

27:43.833 --> 27:45.500
[Mayor Kingpin] BB Urich.

27:46.917 --> 27:48.750
My useful little pawn.

27:48.833 --> 27:51.750
Look at how she sells my lies so well.

27:51.833 --> 27:55.125
Her uncle, Ben Urich,
would be so disappointed in her,

27:55.208 --> 27:57.458
but that's what got him killed.

27:57.542 --> 27:59.250
[laughing]

27:59.333 --> 28:03.292
Anyway, it's your favorite mayor,
Wilson Fisk.

28:03.375 --> 28:05.500
Speaking of what a great mayor I am,

28:05.583 --> 28:08.542
I made so much money off that secret port

28:08.625 --> 28:11.000
for my rich and criminal friends,

28:11.083 --> 28:12.917
making sure the rich get richer

28:13.000 --> 28:15.000
and you stay poorer!

28:15.083 --> 28:18.667
Uh-oh. Looks like I spoke too soon.
Someone caught me.

28:18.750 --> 28:21.500
Spoiled again by that dastardly do-gooder.

28:21.583 --> 28:24.083
I hope he didn't find my illegal goods.

28:24.167 --> 28:25.792
Don't worry, I'll get him in the end.

28:25.875 --> 28:28.708
Just don't you dare try to dig into
what I'm really doing.

28:28.792 --> 28:30.792
That's all for now, and remember,

28:30.875 --> 28:32.208
I love you, New York.

28:38.208 --> 28:40.042
[indistinct chatter]

28:47.875 --> 28:49.417
BB!

28:49.500 --> 28:51.583
Whoa, whoa, chill, chill.

28:51.667 --> 28:52.792
-Hi.
-I'm chill.

28:52.875 --> 28:54.917
-Yeah.
-Thank you so much for coming.

28:55.792 --> 28:57.833
[chuckles] Dude, what the fuck?

28:57.917 --> 28:59.833
Yeah, right? It's pretty dope.

29:01.042 --> 29:03.958
No, dope is any place in Manhattan
without eight roommates.

29:04.042 --> 29:06.417
This is two steps beyond that.

29:06.500 --> 29:08.833
Well, I will remind you

29:08.917 --> 29:11.625
I am Deputy Mayor now, Miss Urich.

29:11.708 --> 29:13.833
Oh, yes, you remind me all the time.

29:14.708 --> 29:17.250
And even on that salary,
you can't afford this.

29:17.333 --> 29:21.167
No, it's perfect. Fisk owns the building,
so he cut me a deal.

29:21.250 --> 29:24.792
Daniel, Fisk shouldn't be involved in
any of his old businesses.

29:24.875 --> 29:26.792
No, no, no, he's all legit.

29:26.875 --> 29:29.875
He put everything he owns into a trust,
which, you know--

29:29.958 --> 29:31.625
Buck Cashman administers.

29:31.708 --> 29:35.667
Look, Daniel,
you have to be careful, okay?

29:35.750 --> 29:38.833
Fisk is playing a ten-dimensional game
and if that comes crashing down,

29:38.917 --> 29:40.500
he's not gonna be the one that gets hurt.

29:41.625 --> 29:44.792
No, I know, I know. I appreciate that.

29:44.875 --> 29:46.500
I appreciate you.

29:46.583 --> 29:49.958
By the way, you killed it with
New York's Back and Better Than Ever.

29:50.042 --> 29:51.417
Everyone was stoked.

29:51.500 --> 29:53.792
-[chuckles] Yeah, thanks.
-Yeah.

30:05.667 --> 30:06.750
[in English] We're closed.

30:08.417 --> 30:10.167
[Matt] Fisk's Task Force do this?

30:12.167 --> 30:13.250
Please.

30:14.833 --> 30:16.125
It's none of your concern.

30:17.083 --> 30:18.708
Yeah, it is. I'm a lawyer.

30:19.667 --> 30:22.917
I feel you run a little side hustle,
getting people out of New York.

30:24.333 --> 30:26.417
That's why he came to you, isn't it?
Achilleo?

30:28.458 --> 30:29.542
I think, uh...

30:30.542 --> 30:32.250
we might be on the same team here.

30:33.500 --> 30:35.083
-Murdock?
-Mmm-hmm.

30:38.000 --> 30:39.542
[speaks Cypriot Greek]

30:43.792 --> 30:47.625
[in English] Aren't you supposed to be
missing, Mr. Murdock, or dead?

30:47.708 --> 30:50.083
Yeah. There's a lot of that
going around these days.

30:50.167 --> 30:51.708
Don't remind me.

30:53.667 --> 30:56.500
Look, Achilleo and Christofi
are in a lot of trouble,

30:56.583 --> 30:58.500
and I'd like to help
protect them if I can.

30:59.542 --> 31:02.750
Achilleo was supposed
to go to Toronto tonight.

31:02.833 --> 31:04.875
And a plane to Nicosia, but...

31:05.667 --> 31:08.458
You just point me in the right direction,
I'll find him.

31:09.375 --> 31:13.625
Task Force took him...
which means nobody finds him.

31:13.708 --> 31:15.833
What about Christofi?

31:15.917 --> 31:17.500
If they got him too,

31:18.167 --> 31:19.333
no one can help him.

31:20.333 --> 31:22.583
Not even the lawyer from Hell's Kitchen.

31:24.708 --> 31:25.792
Yeah, maybe not.

31:27.500 --> 31:29.000
But we have to try, don't we?

31:29.417 --> 31:30.750
[chuckles softly]

31:31.708 --> 31:32.708
Yes.

31:33.917 --> 31:34.917
Yes.

31:35.583 --> 31:36.875
We are doomed to try.

31:42.625 --> 31:44.667
[screaming in pain]

31:48.667 --> 31:51.667
I told you, I did what I was told.

31:52.667 --> 31:53.833
The devil came.

31:53.917 --> 31:56.417
I sank the ship. It was supposed to sink.

31:58.583 --> 32:00.083
By "devil" you mean Daredevil?

32:01.042 --> 32:03.250
Yes, yes, yes. Daredevil devil...

32:03.333 --> 32:04.750
[breathing heavily]

32:05.750 --> 32:06.917
Hey, hey.

32:08.875 --> 32:10.250
Where's Christofi?

32:10.333 --> 32:12.042
I don't know.

32:16.167 --> 32:17.292
[groans]

32:20.667 --> 32:21.750
Why'd you run?

32:23.750 --> 32:24.833
[groaning]

32:24.917 --> 32:26.458
[Buck] Honestly, mate,

32:26.542 --> 32:29.333
d'you ever think maybe you enjoy
your work a bit too much?

32:33.000 --> 32:35.583
[Powell] He confirmed it was Daredevil
on the boat.

32:35.667 --> 32:37.750
[Buck] Yeah. Top tip.

32:37.833 --> 32:40.833
Smashing someone's face in
can make them reluctant to comply.

32:42.208 --> 32:44.875
Next time, maybe pop the kettle on. Yeah?

32:44.958 --> 32:46.958
Get them talking over a nice cup of tea.

32:48.750 --> 32:49.875
Just a thought.

32:51.958 --> 32:53.083
[laughs]

32:54.125 --> 32:55.208
Now, do you mind?

33:00.792 --> 33:01.875
Sorry about him.

33:03.167 --> 33:04.250
He's new.

33:04.958 --> 33:06.292
I did what I was told.

33:07.208 --> 33:08.792
I... I just want to go home.

33:10.083 --> 33:11.167
Yeah, 'course you do.

33:13.500 --> 33:14.583
You know what?

33:16.500 --> 33:17.958
I think that can be arranged.

33:18.042 --> 33:19.583
[breathing deeply]

33:35.458 --> 33:36.708
-[gun fires]
-[groans]

33:43.000 --> 33:44.208
[sighs]

33:50.875 --> 33:52.375
[sighs heavily]

33:54.250 --> 33:55.583
Yeah, thank you, Buck.

33:58.083 --> 33:59.292
[cell phone clicks]

33:59.667 --> 34:01.167
[cell phone clatters on table]

34:01.875 --> 34:02.958
So...

34:04.333 --> 34:08.500
do we speak freely in front of the missus,
or, I mean, everyone has their own...

34:08.583 --> 34:10.667
[chuckles] ...protocols.

34:13.167 --> 34:15.333
Do you try to be abrasive?

34:15.417 --> 34:17.292
Is it part of your tradecraft?

34:18.625 --> 34:20.500
I am what I am, Mrs. Fisk.

34:22.042 --> 34:23.625
I doubt that very much.

34:24.167 --> 34:26.083
-[Charles] Mmm.
-Vanessa, she...

34:27.333 --> 34:30.792
She's privy to all my business dealings,
and I hers.

34:33.667 --> 34:36.417
Well, I didn't mean to offend, so--

34:36.500 --> 34:37.750
But you have.

34:41.792 --> 34:44.542
And I don't appreciate you
grandstanding in my office.

34:45.625 --> 34:49.500
Well, that's funny. I would have called
that divine fucking intervention.

34:49.583 --> 34:50.833
[chuckles softly]

34:54.875 --> 34:57.000
Look, Mr. Mayor, um...

34:57.083 --> 35:02.250
the people I work for are very grateful
for the use of your very special port.

35:03.250 --> 35:08.083
But this is now going kind of like
eight different ways of fucked up, right?

35:08.167 --> 35:09.250
I'm handling it.

35:09.333 --> 35:13.458
My Task Force
is organizing a Salvage Team.

35:16.583 --> 35:17.667
No.

35:22.250 --> 35:23.875
Uh...

35:23.958 --> 35:26.417
Most of my job is... is logistics.

35:26.500 --> 35:28.417
But people don't know that, but it's true.

35:28.500 --> 35:30.125
Like, the corpses, that's easy.

35:30.208 --> 35:33.125
Just make sure they sink
to the river bottom and they stay there.

35:33.208 --> 35:38.542
But moving 30 tons of military ordnance
across a major metropolitan area

35:38.625 --> 35:40.833
without a single fucking person
knowing about it,

35:40.917 --> 35:43.333
that's not easy, man.
It's... I mean... [chuckles]

35:43.958 --> 35:46.292
But it is absolutely necessary.

35:47.125 --> 35:50.417
My men, they're effective.
They're very loyal.

35:51.042 --> 35:52.250
Great.

35:52.333 --> 35:55.708
So you have no problem killing them
after they've unloaded the boat.

35:55.792 --> 35:56.792
Right?

36:00.167 --> 36:02.583
Good men are hard to come by.

36:03.250 --> 36:08.333
I could put together a little night crew,
decent workers, nothing special.

36:08.417 --> 36:10.375
You know, sailors from all over the world.

36:10.458 --> 36:14.083
Easy enough to make them disappear
in an industrial accident,

36:14.167 --> 36:17.750
after they unload the goods
into your Red Hook warehouse.

36:19.375 --> 36:20.667
Obviously, it's up to you.

36:24.000 --> 36:26.333
And nothing gets traced back to us.

36:28.333 --> 36:29.417
Or you...

36:30.417 --> 36:31.500
Mr. Charles.

36:32.458 --> 36:33.708
Whatever your name is.

36:34.542 --> 36:36.167
Lovely lady is correct.

36:37.083 --> 36:38.208
No, nothing.

36:39.125 --> 36:41.417
That circle is complete.

36:43.042 --> 36:45.583
Well, it seems our interests are aligned.

36:46.583 --> 36:47.583
They are.

37:12.375 --> 37:13.458
It's my inside guy.

37:14.292 --> 37:15.542
Well, "source."

37:15.625 --> 37:16.833
Only he doesn't know it.

37:18.625 --> 37:19.708
Do you like him?

37:22.083 --> 37:26.167
I mean, he grows on you,
but, no, not like that.

37:26.250 --> 37:29.083
[chuckles softly]
Good. Could get complicated.

37:30.708 --> 37:32.542
Does he have any idea what you're up to?

37:32.625 --> 37:33.708
No.

37:35.292 --> 37:36.375
Maybe. I don't know.

37:37.542 --> 37:38.792
[Karen] Mmm.

37:39.500 --> 37:41.750
You know, your uncle
used to say something.

37:41.833 --> 37:44.667
Took me a little too long
to figure out what he meant. But...

37:45.292 --> 37:47.208
He said the easiest people to manipulate

37:48.083 --> 37:49.167
are manipulators.

37:50.625 --> 37:54.333
Never forget, BB, we are manipulators.

37:55.500 --> 37:59.542
Is this some, like, sisterhood,
"here endeth the lesson" type shit?

37:59.625 --> 38:02.458
[laughs] No. No, it's, um...

38:04.042 --> 38:07.125
more like an
"I don't want you to die" type of shit.

38:09.208 --> 38:10.208
Yeah.

38:11.500 --> 38:14.167
I do not want you to follow
in the footsteps of your uncle.

38:16.542 --> 38:18.500
You guys were close, right?

38:21.917 --> 38:23.875
[chuckles] Yeah, he's, um...

38:25.250 --> 38:27.792
He's a big part
of why I'm here with you right now.

38:30.083 --> 38:31.292
'Cause Fisk killed him.

38:33.083 --> 38:34.083
Yes.

38:37.250 --> 38:38.292
And I, um...

38:39.500 --> 38:41.167
I have a lot of guilt about that.

38:43.375 --> 38:45.500
I'm pretty sure Ben died to save me.

38:52.583 --> 38:53.792
-Shit.
-Yeah.

38:56.333 --> 38:58.958
You know, there's a lot
of dead bodies behind us, BB.

39:00.792 --> 39:02.958
I think maybe the best way
to honor them...

39:04.333 --> 39:05.667
would be not to join them.

39:08.792 --> 39:09.917
Take care of yourself.

39:14.500 --> 39:17.458
[Heather on recording] "At times
I feel like smashing things."

39:17.542 --> 39:21.083
[Jack chuckles] False.

39:21.167 --> 39:22.875
[Heather] "No one seems to understand me."

39:24.833 --> 39:25.917
[Jack] False.

39:26.417 --> 39:28.542
[Heather] "I'm often the smartest person
in the room."

39:29.125 --> 39:31.375
-[cell phone beeps]
-[Jack] True.

39:31.958 --> 39:34.125
-Hello?
-[Hochberg] Dr. Glenn.

39:34.208 --> 39:37.417
It's Ben Hochberg.
I'm just prepping my opener,

39:37.500 --> 39:41.167
and I'm looking over
your psych eval on Jacques Duquesne.

39:41.250 --> 39:44.583
[Heather chuckles]
I'm just looking over his MMPI.

39:44.667 --> 39:47.958
Um, well, call it serendipity, then.

39:48.042 --> 39:50.625
That's, uh, kind of what I wanted
to talk to you about.

39:50.708 --> 39:53.208
Your contemporaneous notes are fantastic.

39:53.292 --> 39:55.125
His, uh, his hostility,

39:55.208 --> 39:58.083
his hatred of authority, all... All great.

39:58.750 --> 39:59.750
Um...

39:59.833 --> 40:03.167
It does get a little wonky in the data.

40:04.625 --> 40:05.750
How do you mean?

40:05.833 --> 40:09.667
Well, Dr. Glenn, you have a PhD,
my jurors have the Internet.

40:09.750 --> 40:13.417
If I can convince them
that Duquesne is a sociopath,

40:13.500 --> 40:18.542
that might have a much easier time
sending him back into a deep, dark hole.

40:18.625 --> 40:19.625
[thumping loudly]

40:20.625 --> 40:24.500
And, uh, since you're checking
over the answers anyway...

40:35.792 --> 40:37.167
Dr. Glenn, are you there?

40:39.417 --> 40:40.417
Dr. Glenn?

40:42.292 --> 40:44.292
I'm sorry. Um...

40:44.375 --> 40:48.125
Yeah, it's... Of course it's possible
I entered the data wrong.

40:48.625 --> 40:49.917
That is great.

40:51.125 --> 40:53.042
Mayor Fisk said you would be helpful.

40:53.125 --> 40:55.750
He's a very big fan of yours, you know.

40:56.500 --> 40:57.500
As am I.

40:58.167 --> 40:59.833
Thank you. I appreciate it.

40:59.917 --> 41:02.167
Whenever you're done,
if you could send me over

41:02.250 --> 41:06.250
a corrected copy of the data,
that'd be great.

41:06.333 --> 41:08.708
Absolutely.
You'll have it by the end of the day.

41:10.250 --> 41:14.458
One of these days, we should have a drink,
don't you think?

41:18.458 --> 41:20.583
[Heather on recording]
"Evil spirits possess me at times."

41:23.375 --> 41:24.833
I beg your pardon?

41:24.917 --> 41:26.542
[Heather] Just answer the question.

41:26.625 --> 41:29.208
"Evil spirits possess me at times."

41:34.000 --> 41:35.083
[Jack] False.

41:48.542 --> 41:49.667
[sniffles]

42:00.417 --> 42:03.625
-[Matt grunting]
-[♪ indie rock music playing faintly]

42:08.167 --> 42:10.833
I will never figure out how you do that.

42:10.917 --> 42:14.167
You know, years of brutal training
from a borderline psychotic sensei.

42:15.792 --> 42:18.333
-That all?
-There is nothing to it. Here.

42:18.417 --> 42:19.958
[Matt breathing heavily]

42:20.542 --> 42:21.625
[Karen clears throat]

42:29.375 --> 42:31.375
This restaurateur in Astoria.

42:32.125 --> 42:34.875
She was trying to get
Achilleo to Cyprus. Nice.

42:34.958 --> 42:36.417
She's there if we need her.

42:37.125 --> 42:40.083
Good. And we need more people
making trouble for Fisk,

42:40.167 --> 42:42.542
especially with the vigilante trials
coming up.

42:47.500 --> 42:48.875
Hey! [breathing heavily]

42:48.958 --> 42:50.125
-It's too fast.
-Sorry.

42:51.000 --> 42:52.167
Sorry.

42:52.875 --> 42:53.917
Hey, you okay?

42:54.000 --> 42:56.958
[breathing heavily]
Yeah. Yeah. Just the trials are just...

42:59.708 --> 43:00.792
You miss it?

43:02.583 --> 43:04.208
-Do I miss it?
-You know...

43:05.375 --> 43:06.542
Being Matt Murdock?

43:09.125 --> 43:10.458
Nelson, Murdock, and Page...

43:15.958 --> 43:17.708
Wow, I don't know. Just...

43:19.125 --> 43:21.083
Just trying to focus on moving forward.

43:22.667 --> 43:24.583
[exhales heavily] Yeah, I...

43:25.750 --> 43:27.917
Yeah, I guess, sometimes I do. Yeah.

43:29.875 --> 43:30.875
You?

43:33.708 --> 43:34.792
Every damn day.

43:35.667 --> 43:40.167
♪ It's crazy I know
I've got nowhere to go ♪

43:40.792 --> 43:44.958
♪ But up here, I wear my seatbelt ♪

43:45.042 --> 43:46.750
[Karen exhales heavily]

43:49.667 --> 43:50.792
[Ariana] Everything is good?

43:51.875 --> 43:53.875
So happy to have you back.

43:53.958 --> 43:55.250
-[chuckles]
-Thank you.

44:08.292 --> 44:09.542
[door creaks open]

44:32.375 --> 44:35.083
-[♪ R&B song playing on record]
-♪ Gee whiz ♪

44:35.167 --> 44:37.333
-[objects clattering]
-[Cherry breathing heavily]

44:37.417 --> 44:39.458
♪ Look at his eyes ♪

44:39.542 --> 44:40.583
[Cherry] Kirsten...

44:41.292 --> 44:43.083
David and fucking Goliath.

44:44.583 --> 44:47.708
♪ How they hypnotize ♪

44:47.792 --> 44:49.292
[banging on door]

44:50.000 --> 44:51.417
[officer] Task Force. Open up.

44:51.500 --> 44:53.125
[sighs heavily]

44:55.417 --> 44:57.500
-[♪ song continues playing]
-[sighs]

44:57.958 --> 44:59.042
[Cherry] What do you want?

45:00.208 --> 45:01.458
[officer] Just wanna talk.

45:02.167 --> 45:03.583
[Cherry] Unless you got a warrant...

45:05.083 --> 45:06.583
the door stays closed.

45:07.500 --> 45:09.708
[officer] Come on, Cherry,
it don't gotta be like that.

45:11.292 --> 45:12.583
Yeah. Yeah, I do.

45:13.208 --> 45:14.917
-[crashing]
-[officer grunting]

45:15.000 --> 45:16.833
[all grunting]

45:23.833 --> 45:25.542
-Sit down.
-[Cherry groans]

45:27.667 --> 45:30.500
Why are you and a bunch of loser cops
looking for Greek sailors?

45:30.583 --> 45:32.333
Which loser cops are we talking about?

45:32.417 --> 45:33.917
-[grunts]
-[groans]

45:34.000 --> 45:35.625
-[officer laughing]
-[groans]

45:36.458 --> 45:37.583
I can do this all night.

45:37.667 --> 45:39.000
Yeah, you hit like a kid.

45:39.083 --> 45:42.000
-[officer grunting]
-[Cherry groaning]

45:43.875 --> 45:45.417
[coughing]

45:47.208 --> 45:49.000
[officers panting]

45:49.917 --> 45:51.500
[groaning]

45:54.333 --> 45:55.583
-[metal clanks]
-[officer grunts]

45:55.667 --> 45:57.833
-He's here. Daredevil--
-[Daredevil grunts]

45:57.917 --> 45:59.167
[Daredevil] You okay?

45:59.250 --> 46:00.500
No, I'm not okay.

46:00.583 --> 46:02.125
-Can you stand? There you go.
-[groaning]

46:03.417 --> 46:05.958
[overlapping voices echoing]

46:06.042 --> 46:07.167
Fuck.

46:08.375 --> 46:09.875
-No...
-Your heart.

46:09.958 --> 46:11.250
I suck. [groans]

46:11.333 --> 46:13.833
Sure could take a punch a lot better
ten years ago.

46:13.917 --> 46:15.583
[groaning, panting]

46:24.375 --> 46:27.458
-[♪ song continues playing]
-[Cherry breathing hoarsely]

46:33.000 --> 46:36.875
-[metal clanking]
-[all grunting]

46:43.000 --> 46:45.083
-[yelling]
-[grunts]

46:45.167 --> 46:47.750
-[continues yelling]
-[grunting continues]

46:54.167 --> 46:57.250
-[breathing weakly]
-[heart beating rapidly]

46:59.625 --> 47:01.500
[Karen crying] Foggy...

47:02.708 --> 47:04.667
[Daredevil grunting]

47:05.417 --> 47:07.250
[ears ringing]

47:13.875 --> 47:16.042
-[heart beating rapidly]
-[groaning weakly]

47:17.667 --> 47:19.375
[Daredevil groans, grunts]

47:19.458 --> 47:20.917
[all grunting]

47:25.583 --> 47:27.542
[Daredevil straining]

47:29.417 --> 47:32.292
-[ears ringing]
-[heart beating rapidly]

47:32.375 --> 47:34.458
[Daredevil groaning]

47:38.792 --> 47:40.292
Holy shit!

47:41.292 --> 47:42.292
It's Matt Murdock.

47:43.625 --> 47:45.292
[song distorts]

47:46.625 --> 47:47.958
-[gun cocks]
-[silenced gunshots]

47:48.042 --> 47:50.458
[officers groaning]

47:51.792 --> 47:54.042
[Cherry breathing heavily]

48:00.292 --> 48:02.083
[gasps, breathing heavily]

48:08.583 --> 48:12.917
♪ Gee whiz ♪

48:14.042 --> 48:17.583
♪ Look at his eyes ♪

48:19.083 --> 48:25.458
♪ Gee whiz, how they hypnotize ♪

48:27.292 --> 48:32.625
♪ He's got everything a girl could want ♪

48:32.708 --> 48:39.250
♪ Man, oh, man, what a prize! ♪

48:41.292 --> 48:43.917
♪ Ooh, ooh! ♪

48:44.000 --> 48:47.292
♪ Gee whiz ♪

48:47.375 --> 48:51.417
♪ He's all the joy ♪

48:52.500 --> 48:54.958
♪ Gee whiz ♪

48:55.042 --> 48:59.333
♪ I could find in a boy ♪

49:00.958 --> 49:06.042
♪ He's awful nice, it's paradise ♪

49:06.125 --> 49:12.667
♪ I hope I'm not his decoy ♪

49:13.417 --> 49:16.875
♪ Decoy ♪

49:18.833 --> 49:25.417
♪ Heaven up above knows how much ♪

49:26.500 --> 49:32.458
♪ I love that fella so ♪

49:35.042 --> 49:41.958
♪ Angels sing of a love like this ♪

49:43.708 --> 49:48.542
♪ I hope our love will grow and grow ♪

49:48.625 --> 49:53.125
♪ Oh, gee whiz ♪

49:54.375 --> 49:58.500
♪ I love that guy ♪

49:58.583 --> 50:02.000
♪ Gee whiz ♪

50:02.083 --> 50:05.583
♪ My, my, oh my ♪

50:06.917 --> 50:11.125
♪ There are things we could do ♪

50:11.208 --> 50:15.458
♪ I could say I love you ♪

50:15.542 --> 50:20.500
♪ But all I can say is ♪

50:21.375 --> 50:27.833
♪ Gee whiz! ♪

50:32.375 --> 50:34.083
[song ends]
